TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = non_zero_random(-3,3,1);
$am = -$a;

$p1 = $a - 4;
$p2 = $a - 3;
$x1 = random($p1,$p2,1);
$y1 = 1/($x1 + $am);
$m1 = -($x1+$am)**(-2);

BEGIN_TEXT
If \( f(x) = \frac{1}{x + $am} \), find \( f'( $x1 ) \), using the
definition of derivative. \( f'( $x1 ) \) is the limit as \(x\to\) \{ans_rule()\}
of the expression
$BR
\{ans_rule(40)\}
$BR
The value of this limit is
\{ans_rule(20) \}
$BR
END_TEXT

$ans1 = $x1;
$ans2 = "(1/(x + $am) - $y1)/(x - $x1)";
$ans = $m1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(fun_cmp($ans2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans));


